3
00:00:36.078 --> 00:00:37.329
THE K2

4
00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:54.889
This is the second meeting I mentioned.

5
00:01:03.355 --> 00:01:04.315
Shoot her.

6
00:01:04.982 --> 00:01:05.816
Shoot.

7
00:01:08.277 --> 00:01:09.111
Shoot her!

8
00:01:18.662 --> 00:01:19.872
Help me!

9
00:01:20.998 --> 00:01:22.666
Please help me!

10
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:25.628
Get me out of here!

11
00:01:27.087 --> 00:01:29.340
Shoot her!

12
00:01:32.259 --> 00:01:33.928
I said shoot her!

13
00:01:34.011 --> 00:01:35.471
Shoot her now!

14
00:01:35.554 --> 00:01:37.348
Kill her!

15
00:01:39.058 --> 00:01:41.769
Shoot her! Kill her!

16
00:01:42.561 --> 00:01:45.314
Shoot her! Hurry up and shoot!

17
00:01:46.232 --> 00:01:47.983
Kill her!

18
00:01:48.692 --> 00:01:51.070
I said kill her!

19
00:01:58.035 --> 00:01:58.994
I guess there were...

20
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:05.835
others who wanted you dead. too.

21
00:02:11.006 --> 00:02:11.924
Ms. Choi!

22
00:02:33.237 --> 00:02:34.196
Lower your guns.

23
00:02:34.989 --> 00:02:35.823
Lower them!

24
00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:37.449
She's in danger.

25
00:02:39.952 --> 00:02:40.870
Everyone. out.

26
00:02:41.912 --> 00:02:42.872
Get a car ready.

27
00:02:46.709 --> 00:02:47.877
Do as he says.

28
00:02:50.838 --> 00:02:51.755
Get Ms. Choi's car.

29
00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:03.559
You came back to kill me?

30
00:03:04.435 --> 00:03:05.519
But unfortunately.

31
00:03:06.395 --> 00:03:07.229
if you kill me.

32
00:03:08.272 --> 00:03:10.357
you won't make it out of here alive.

33
00:03:10.608 --> 00:03:12.526
I don't think you can afford

34
00:03:13.444 --> 00:03:15.863
to worry about anyone else right now.

35
00:03:15.946 --> 00:03:17.406
You should drop your gun

36
00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:18.824
and beg for your life.

37
00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:21.785
That's your best chance of survival.

38
00:03:24.663 --> 00:03:28.375
I already have the trigger pulled halfway.

39
00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:29.668
And...

40
00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:36.717
the trigger on this Walther
is pretty sensitive.

41
00:03:40.429 --> 00:03:41.263
Okay.

42
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:42.848
Turn the car around.

43
00:03:42.932 --> 00:03:43.933
And step on it.

44
00:03:48.687 --> 00:03:49.563
What's going on?

45
00:03:49.647 --> 00:03:52.066
Ms. Choi's been taken hostage.

46
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:57.738
Pull over up there.

47
00:03:58.864 --> 00:03:59.698
Sir?

48
00:04:02.952 --> 00:04:04.119
You have any cigarettes?

49
00:04:20.511 --> 00:04:21.428
What are you doing?

50
00:04:24.431 --> 00:04:25.557
I just sent an email.

51
00:04:31.021 --> 00:04:32.064
And attached to it

52
00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:34.775
is a recording of everything
you said and did here

53
00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.069
on video.

54
00:04:39.029 --> 00:04:40.698
To the media. Prosecutor's Office.

55
00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:42.908
and the Blue House.

56
00:04:44.326 --> 00:04:45.953
But don't be too sad.

57
00:04:46.036 --> 00:04:47.371
I scheduled it

58
00:04:47.454 --> 00:04:49.790
to go out automatically after 24 hours.

59
00:04:55.129 --> 00:04:56.088
So...

60
00:05:00.801 --> 00:05:04.138
Leave me and the people around me...

61
00:05:05.681 --> 00:05:06.807
alone.

62
00:05:08.225 --> 00:05:09.977
If I end up dying.

63
00:05:10.936 --> 00:05:13.105
no one will be able to delay it.

64
00:05:15.357 --> 00:05:16.567
So all you have to do

65
00:05:17.151 --> 00:05:19.528
is pray that I'm safe and sound

66
00:05:21.739 --> 00:05:22.614
every day.

67
00:05:27.578 --> 00:05:28.412
See this?

68
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:45.929
-No!
-No!

69
00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:52.311
I want you to go outside and tell them.

70
00:05:53.187 --> 00:05:55.355
If your security does something foolish

71
00:05:55.856 --> 00:05:57.191
and has me killed.

72
00:06:01.737 --> 00:06:02.696
you'd be in trouble.

73
00:06:11.163 --> 00:06:13.957
Chief Ju. isn't it your job to protect me?

74
00:06:14.291 --> 00:06:15.417
-Yes. sir.
-So...

75
00:06:16.502 --> 00:06:19.588
if you take me home now.
I'll be in danger.

76
00:06:21.673 --> 00:06:22.508
Won't I?

77
00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:26.095
I'm heading there
to keep the promise I made you.

78
00:06:26.553 --> 00:06:28.514
What? Promise?

79
00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:29.973
Right now.

80
00:06:31.975 --> 00:06:33.143
Anna is at your house.

81
00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:40.234
What are you doing? Step on it!

82
00:06:47.282 --> 00:06:48.617
{\an8}EPISODE 3

83
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.369
{\an8}Gosh. Ms. Choi!

84
00:06:51.745 --> 00:06:52.579
{\an8}Good evening.

85
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:02.631
{\an8}Hello. Thank you for your hard work.

86
00:07:03.048 --> 00:07:04.508
{\an8}Please. don't mention it.

87
00:07:04.591 --> 00:07:06.135
{\an8}A motorbike thief's causing

88
00:07:06.218 --> 00:07:07.803
{\an8}a ruckus on this quiet street.

89
00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:34.204
Ms. Choi is going to drive herself?

90
00:07:44.131 --> 00:07:45.966
-Hurry up!
-Yes. ma'am.

91
00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:02.482
I underestimated you.

92
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:05.861
Or rather.
you paid too much attention to me.

93
00:08:06.862 --> 00:08:09.573
I didn't even care
about your husband's affair.

94
00:08:09.865 --> 00:08:12.701
And I didn't care if you cared or not.

95
00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:15.746
Fine.

96
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.207
I'll admit my mistake.

97
00:08:19.416 --> 00:08:21.585
Then. shall we start negotiating?

98
00:08:22.002 --> 00:08:22.961
Negotiating?

99
00:08:23.045 --> 00:08:24.463
Name your price.

100
00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:30.344
Sell my email?

101
00:08:32.095 --> 00:08:34.723
Everything in this world has a price.

102
00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:37.434
Okay.

103
00:08:38.310 --> 00:08:39.519
The email probably costs

104
00:08:40.145 --> 00:08:41.730
as much as my life.

105
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:43.774
Because if I hand it over. I'll die.

106
00:08:44.608 --> 00:08:45.817
Give me a figure.

107
00:08:46.193 --> 00:08:49.696
I'll double it.

108
00:08:54.409 --> 00:08:55.285
Then...

109
00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:57.663
what's your price?

110
00:08:59.623 --> 00:09:01.333
If I asked your husband

111
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:03.085
to choose between selling

112
00:09:03.168 --> 00:09:05.712
you or the email. which would he choose?

113
00:09:07.089 --> 00:09:09.258
Would he give up the presidency for you

114
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:12.719
or sell you for the presidency?

115
00:09:15.138 --> 00:09:17.015
What? Not confident he'd choose you?

116
00:09:19.017 --> 00:09:21.436
Are you worth less than the email?

117
00:09:40.205 --> 00:09:41.999
Your people don't listen.

118
00:10:00.142 --> 00:10:01.059
Mr. Kim!

119
00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:08.525
I'm sorry. sir.
We failed to protect Ms. Choi.

120
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:10.485
Damn it. Where's Anna?

121
00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:12.404
She's safe. sir.

122
00:10:16.408 --> 00:10:17.242
Where is she now?

123
00:10:26.918 --> 00:10:29.629
Should I get Miss Anna for you?

124
00:11:02.454 --> 00:11:03.413
No. it's all right.

125
00:11:05.707 --> 00:11:07.959
I need to get some rest.

126
00:11:18.095 --> 00:11:18.970
I'm tired.

127
00:11:19.971 --> 00:11:20.889
Of course. sir.

128
00:12:20.615 --> 00:12:22.993
Hey. can you slow down?

129
00:12:23.577 --> 00:12:24.828
It's not me.

130
00:12:25.412 --> 00:12:26.288
Something's wrong.

131
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:37.382
The brakes won't work!

132
00:12:44.389 --> 00:12:45.474
They hacked the car.

133
00:12:47.601 --> 00:12:50.187
I guess there were others
who wanted you dead. too.

134
00:12:51.021 --> 00:12:52.522
What? Who?

135
00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:53.815
Them.

136
00:13:04.451 --> 00:13:05.327
Who are they?

137
00:13:05.911 --> 00:13:07.787
-"They"?
-A motorcycle's chasing her.

138
00:13:07.871 --> 00:13:08.705
A motorcycle?

139
00:13:27.224 --> 00:13:28.850
It's no use. It's bulletproof.

140
00:13:50.622 --> 00:13:52.207
The intersection's ahead!

141
00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:08.181
Now's the time.
Move over to the passenger seat.

142
00:14:12.561 --> 00:14:14.729
She's going too fast. Something's off.

143
00:14:14.813 --> 00:14:16.940
They saw us. Drive faster!

144
00:14:17.399 --> 00:14:18.733
Don't lose them.

145
00:14:23.113 --> 00:14:24.281
They're switching spots.

146
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:26.199
What? Ms. Choi and the hostage taker?

147
00:14:26.283 --> 00:14:28.243
-The motorcycle's still on them?
-Yes.

148
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:31.121
Who the hell are they?

149
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:32.414
What. aren't they a team?

150
00:14:32.497 --> 00:14:34.541
A team wouldn't work together this way.

151
00:14:39.129 --> 00:14:41.089
{\an8}There's a sharp turn in 5 kilometers.

152
00:14:41.590 --> 00:14:43.383
A perfect set up for an accident.

153
00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:17.375
Damn it.

154
00:15:28.720 --> 00:15:29.596
What are you doing?

155
00:15:29.679 --> 00:15:32.057
I can't slow down but I can speed up.

156
00:15:32.140 --> 00:15:34.267
Are you mad? Why would you speed up?

157
00:15:34.351 --> 00:15:36.478
Their remote only works within 20 meters.

158
00:15:37.103 --> 00:15:39.397
That's why they're following so close.

159
00:15:39.481 --> 00:15:41.107
We need to distance ourselves.

160
00:15:41.858 --> 00:15:43.068
so they lose control.

161
00:15:46.821 --> 00:15:48.490
Her car's going even faster.

162
00:15:48.573 --> 00:15:49.616
What should we do?

163
00:15:49.699 --> 00:15:51.284
What do you think?

164
00:15:51.826 --> 00:15:52.702
Hurry up!

165
00:15:54.037 --> 00:15:55.538
We can't lose her!

166
00:15:58.083 --> 00:15:59.209
<i>They're speeding up?</i>

167
00:16:00.335 --> 00:16:02.128
<i>But there's a sharp turn ahead.</i>

168
00:16:59.936 --> 00:17:02.355
Keep pressing until the window rolls down.

169
00:17:17.412 --> 00:17:18.288
We can't lose them!

170
00:17:41.561 --> 00:17:42.729
We're going to lose them!

171
00:17:42.812 --> 00:17:45.023
-Go faster!
-Yes. ma'am.

172
00:17:56.951 --> 00:17:57.786
Okay.

173
00:18:07.337 --> 00:18:08.213
Watch out.

174
00:18:37.242 --> 00:18:38.701
Ms. Kim.

175
00:18:38.785 --> 00:18:41.204
Shots were fired from inside the car.

176
00:18:41.579 --> 00:18:43.289
What? At Ms. Choi?

177
00:18:43.540 --> 00:18:45.583
No. they were shot out the window.

178
00:18:45.667 --> 00:18:47.460
Ms. Choi is safe.

179
00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:53.299
Out the window?

180
00:18:54.259 --> 00:18:55.134
The motorbike.

181
00:18:55.844 --> 00:18:57.136
Handle the motorbike now!

182
00:19:01.391 --> 00:19:04.853
Your agents are finally starting
to use their heads.

183
00:19:04.936 --> 00:19:06.104
A little late though.

184
00:19:39.554 --> 00:19:40.430
Kill them.

185
00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:00.677
My goodness! What in the world?

186
00:21:11.854 --> 00:21:13.272
-Fire!
-Fire!

187
00:21:34.419 --> 00:21:35.753
Hey!

188
00:21:37.463 --> 00:21:39.716
Ms. Kim.

189
00:21:41.801 --> 00:21:43.052
Hey. wake up!

190
00:21:43.594 --> 00:21:44.470
Hey.

191
00:21:45.013 --> 00:21:46.139
Wake up!

192
00:21:46.556 --> 00:21:47.390
Hey!

193
00:21:52.770 --> 00:21:54.689
Ms. Kim! Are you all right?

194
00:21:55.398 --> 00:21:56.566
Where's Ms. Choi?

195
00:22:00.611 --> 00:22:01.571
No!

196
00:22:18.129 --> 00:22:19.672
Ms. Kim. it's too late.

197
00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:20.798
It'll explode.

198
00:22:21.674 --> 00:22:23.843
Cut the nonsense! Go save her now!

199
00:22:24.969 --> 00:22:26.179
No! Stay back!

200
00:22:26.846 --> 00:22:27.722
It's dangerous!

201
00:22:27.805 --> 00:22:28.973
Let go! Move!

202
00:22:29.057 --> 00:22:30.183
-No!
-Let go!

203
00:22:30.266 --> 00:22:31.309
-No!
-Ms. Kim!

204
00:23:02.090 --> 00:23:03.883
-Ms. Choi?
-Ms. Choi!

205
00:24:57.663 --> 00:24:59.832
He's alive. What should we do?

206
00:24:59.916 --> 00:25:01.167
Take him to the infirmary.

207
00:25:01.667 --> 00:25:03.502
-Prepare to question him.
-Yes. ma'am.

208
00:25:04.879 --> 00:25:05.713
Hospital.

209
00:25:07.465 --> 00:25:08.299
Ms. Choi?

210
00:25:08.841 --> 00:25:10.218
To the hospital.

211
00:25:11.052 --> 00:25:13.221
Yes. ma'am. We'll take you there soon.

212
00:25:14.555 --> 00:25:15.640
No.

213
00:25:17.558 --> 00:25:20.728
Take him to the hospital.

214
00:25:22.313 --> 00:25:23.147
What?

215
00:25:30.696 --> 00:25:31.781
We can't...

216
00:25:34.617 --> 00:25:36.244
we can't let him die.

217
00:25:42.333 --> 00:25:44.877
Yes. I know.

218
00:25:50.633 --> 00:25:53.886
<i>No. you don't.</i>

219
00:25:59.058 --> 00:26:00.476
Do you think the sunset

220
00:26:01.852 --> 00:26:04.063
would look even more beautiful in Heaven?

221
00:26:06.274 --> 00:26:07.149
Heaven?

222
00:26:09.902 --> 00:26:11.028
Does such a thing exist?

223
00:26:11.445 --> 00:26:14.824
There's no war in Heaven.

224
00:26:15.199 --> 00:26:17.618
So Korea will be like Heaven too.

225
00:26:18.828 --> 00:26:21.247
Well. it could be like Heaven to some...

226
00:26:24.333 --> 00:26:28.504
or the opposite to others.

227
00:26:30.131 --> 00:26:32.925
And there's 2NE1 in Korea.

228
00:26:33.467 --> 00:26:35.052
That's why it's Heaven.

229
00:26:35.344 --> 00:26:37.763
<i>Who's the best?</i>

230
00:26:40.725 --> 00:26:42.935
What? Did I say it wrong again?

231
00:26:43.561 --> 00:26:44.603
No.

232
00:26:44.687 --> 00:26:46.314
For someone who's never been.

233
00:26:46.397 --> 00:26:47.982
your Korean's pretty good.

234
00:26:48.357 --> 00:26:49.650
You're a genius. Rania.

235
00:26:49.734 --> 00:26:52.236
Well. as a Korean language major.

236
00:26:52.945 --> 00:26:55.239
<i>I'm the best</i>

237
00:26:57.116 --> 00:26:58.576
That's good.

238
00:27:05.916 --> 00:27:07.251
-Rania.
-Yeah?

239
00:27:09.378 --> 00:27:10.421
So...

240
00:27:11.881 --> 00:27:12.715
Actually...

241
00:27:15.426 --> 00:27:17.928
I think I have to go back to Korea.

242
00:27:24.018 --> 00:27:25.186
I won't be able...

243
00:27:28.022 --> 00:27:30.441
to work here anymore.

244
00:27:31.776 --> 00:27:32.860
I know.

245
00:27:33.778 --> 00:27:36.322
You can't help it.

246
00:27:40.868 --> 00:27:43.537
Then. when are you going back?

247
00:27:43.621 --> 00:27:44.705
Want to come with me?

248
00:27:45.164 --> 00:27:45.998
What?

249
00:27:48.626 --> 00:27:49.543
Here.

250
00:27:54.548 --> 00:27:57.009
I mean. if we get wed.

251
00:27:57.510 --> 00:27:59.970
I heard you could get a passport. too.

252
00:28:01.138 --> 00:28:02.223
Wed?

253
00:28:04.308 --> 00:28:06.936
What that means is...

254
00:28:07.019 --> 00:28:09.605
So it means...

255
00:28:10.147 --> 00:28:11.524
getting married.

256
00:28:14.151 --> 00:28:17.530
It was too hard to get a ring around here.

257
00:28:17.613 --> 00:28:20.658
Here's this for now...

258
00:28:23.494 --> 00:28:26.205
But don't get me wrong.
It's just for legal purposes.

259
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:28.999
I wanted to get you out of here.

260
00:28:33.754 --> 00:28:34.630
What's wrong?

261
00:28:35.256 --> 00:28:37.341
Why are you suddenly crying?

262
00:28:37.425 --> 00:28:39.927
I'm not going to...

263
00:28:40.719 --> 00:28:42.805
I mean. you can go with me to Korea.

264
00:28:42.888 --> 00:28:44.807
and if you

265
00:28:44.890 --> 00:28:47.685
really hate it. then...

266
00:28:48.853 --> 00:28:52.440
you can go wherever you want. too.

267
00:28:52.523 --> 00:28:53.441
Yes.

268
00:28:54.567 --> 00:28:55.651
Let's get married.

269
00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:21.028
Don't get any silly ideas.

270
00:30:26.116 --> 00:30:27.326
Please don't.

271
00:30:38.963 --> 00:30:42.299
Hey. I told you we're police!

272
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:44.343
I know.

273
00:30:45.678 --> 00:30:47.596
This is ridiculous.

274
00:30:48.889 --> 00:30:51.642
It's chaos right now.
People think it was terrorism.

275
00:30:52.059 --> 00:30:53.310
And the person in there

276
00:30:53.394 --> 00:30:55.813
is a victim and a key witness.

277
00:30:55.896 --> 00:30:58.107
You're obstructing justice right now!

278
00:30:58.607 --> 00:30:59.942
We know nothing about that.

279
00:31:01.193 --> 00:31:03.946
He needs bed rest until he's stable.

280
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:05.322
Doctor's orders.

281
00:31:05.656 --> 00:31:08.784
But if you insist. go get a warrant.

282
00:31:09.326 --> 00:31:10.411
Got it?

283
00:31:10.995 --> 00:31:12.204
You've got to be kidding.

284
00:31:13.205 --> 00:31:14.290
Who are you guys?

285
00:31:15.374 --> 00:31:17.626
I want to speak to the head of security.

286
00:31:17.710 --> 00:31:18.544
And...

287
00:31:19.253 --> 00:31:21.422
Go and speak with them yourself.

288
00:31:21.797 --> 00:31:23.299
We're not associated with them.

289
00:31:23.882 --> 00:31:25.509
For crying out loud.

290
00:31:26.176 --> 00:31:29.805
It's getting harder and harder
to be the police in this country.

291
00:31:30.639 --> 00:31:31.473
Hey.

292
00:31:33.058 --> 00:31:33.892
Hey!

293
00:31:35.978 --> 00:31:37.855
-Come on. let's go.
-What?

294
00:31:39.189 --> 00:31:40.232
Sir.

295
00:31:40.482 --> 00:31:41.859
We can't just leave.

296
00:31:41.942 --> 00:31:44.069
They're right.
We should do it by the book.

297
00:31:44.153 --> 00:31:45.070
Still...

298
00:31:45.613 --> 00:31:46.947
Who in the world are they?

299
00:31:47.531 --> 00:31:49.325
JSS Security Service.

300
00:31:49.408 --> 00:31:51.285
A security company?

301
00:31:51.702 --> 00:31:54.580
But that's a duty
we should be in charge of.

302
00:31:55.122 --> 00:31:56.206
Those arrogant...

303
00:31:56.290 --> 00:31:58.167
Hey. come here.

304
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:00.377
I said come over here.

305
00:32:01.837 --> 00:32:04.298
Hey. the president of that company

306
00:32:04.381 --> 00:32:06.967
is the former Police Commissioner.

307
00:32:07.051 --> 00:32:10.054
And the former Prosecutor General
is an advisor.

308
00:32:10.137 --> 00:32:11.930
-Prosecutor General?
-Get it?

309
00:32:12.681 --> 00:32:16.143
They're not bodyguards
for some K-pop stars.

310
00:32:16.226 --> 00:32:17.311
You have no idea.

311
00:32:17.394 --> 00:32:18.979
Where's the exit?

312
00:32:20.022 --> 00:32:21.148
Wait. sir.

313
00:32:22.983 --> 00:32:24.985
<i>As you can see in this clip.</i>

314
00:32:25.069 --> 00:32:28.489
<i>Choi Yoo-jin.
wife of Assemblyman Jang Se-joon.</i>

315
00:32:28.572 --> 00:32:31.075
<i>was taken by ambulance
to a hospital last night.</i>

316
00:32:31.575 --> 00:32:34.203
{\an8}<i>Assemblyman Kim. what's your take on this?</i>

317
00:32:34.286 --> 00:32:36.664
{\an8}<i>Well.</i>

318
00:32:36.747 --> 00:32:38.374
<i>there's no other way to put it.</i>

319
00:32:38.666 --> 00:32:40.626
This is a clear act of terrorism.

320
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:45.089
I mean. Korea is an advanced OECD country.

321
00:32:45.464 --> 00:32:47.257
How could such pathetic.

322
00:32:47.341 --> 00:32:49.551
barbaric. and uncivilized act

323
00:32:49.635 --> 00:32:52.596
of political terrorism happen here?

324
00:32:54.640 --> 00:32:55.849
It's deplorable.

325
00:32:56.100 --> 00:32:58.227
But at this point. wouldn't it be hard

326
00:32:58.310 --> 00:32:59.853
to clearly label it

327
00:32:59.937 --> 00:33:01.897
as political terrorism?

328
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:06.402
Isn't this clear enough evidence?

329
00:33:06.652 --> 00:33:07.736
Think about it.

330
00:33:07.820 --> 00:33:09.613
To make it seem like an accident.

331
00:33:09.697 --> 00:33:13.826
using highly advanced technology
to hack vehicles

332
00:33:13.909 --> 00:33:16.870
to commit an act of terror
is enough to say

333
00:33:17.246 --> 00:33:20.541
that such a sophisticated crime

334
00:33:20.624 --> 00:33:24.294
couldn't have been perpetrated
by one person.

335
00:33:24.378 --> 00:33:26.714
-That's what I mean.
-Yes. I suppose.

336
00:33:27.089 --> 00:33:30.175
Still. we have to wait
for the investigation

337
00:33:30.259 --> 00:33:31.635
of the deceased suspects

338
00:33:31.719 --> 00:33:33.971
to find out what the real motivation was.

339
00:33:34.054 --> 00:33:35.347
Yes.

340
00:33:36.098 --> 00:33:38.475
Of course. But...

341
00:33:39.059 --> 00:33:42.271
In all crimes. isn't the primary suspect

342
00:33:42.563 --> 00:33:46.525
the individual or organization
that receives the resulting benefit

343
00:33:46.608 --> 00:33:49.903
from the crime itself?

344
00:33:49.987 --> 00:33:54.533
Assemblyman Kim. what you're saying
does have some merit. especially now.

345
00:33:54.616 --> 00:33:56.452
Having said that.

346
00:33:57.035 --> 00:33:59.121
what you stated just now

347
00:33:59.204 --> 00:34:01.749
could potentially be
a very dangerous statement.

348
00:34:01.832 --> 00:34:05.836
So I mean. what I'm saying is.

349
00:34:06.170 --> 00:34:07.880
{\an8}<i>that could be the case.</i>

350
00:34:07.963 --> 00:34:09.298
{\an8}<i>It's not like I said</i>

351
00:34:09.381 --> 00:34:14.511
<i>that this was committed
by Jang Se-joon's opponents.</i>

352
00:34:16.388 --> 00:34:19.224
<i>And the individual or organization</i>

353
00:34:19.308 --> 00:34:22.728
<i>who'd benefit from this crime...</i>

354
00:34:23.270 --> 00:34:26.523
My. he's a funny man.

355
00:34:26.607 --> 00:34:29.651
He's flat-out said Park Gwan-su did it.

356
00:34:32.404 --> 00:34:34.114
Was that your instruction. Ms. Kim?

357
00:34:34.782 --> 00:34:38.076
No. he did that himself.

358
00:34:38.660 --> 00:34:40.829
Call him after to thank him.

359
00:34:41.079 --> 00:34:42.998
Tell him to visit once I'm discharged.

360
00:34:43.081 --> 00:34:44.500
There's no need for that.

361
00:34:45.083 --> 00:34:46.877
Given all that we do for him.

362
00:34:47.711 --> 00:34:49.463
it's the least he could do for us.

363
00:34:56.386 --> 00:34:57.262
Sir.

364
00:35:01.058 --> 00:35:01.892
Ma'am.

365
00:35:03.352 --> 00:35:05.687
Did you have a restful evening?

366
00:35:06.438 --> 00:35:07.564
Yes. with your help.

367
00:35:08.190 --> 00:35:09.066
Thank you.

368
00:35:09.358 --> 00:35:11.360
Please don't mention it.

369
00:35:11.693 --> 00:35:13.570
It's simply an honor

370
00:35:13.654 --> 00:35:15.197
that you've chosen our hospital.

371
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:18.408
No matter the time. I am at your service.

372
00:35:21.537 --> 00:35:22.538
Right.

373
00:35:23.497 --> 00:35:27.334
How's the man who was brought in with me?

374
00:35:28.961 --> 00:35:29.878
The bodyguard?

375
00:35:33.048 --> 00:35:33.882
The bodyguard?

376
00:35:33.966 --> 00:35:36.552
We treated his fractured left thumb.

377
00:35:36.635 --> 00:35:40.180
He's received a few stitches.
but the CT scan indicated no issues.

378
00:35:40.556 --> 00:35:43.350
It seems he has
a very strong physical makeup.

379
00:35:43.433 --> 00:35:45.185
so he will be fine.

380
00:35:46.812 --> 00:35:49.314
I see. That's a relief.

381
00:35:49.773 --> 00:35:52.901
It seems he's been trained very well.

382
00:35:53.777 --> 00:35:57.072
If you'd been directly exposed
to that kind of shock.

383
00:35:57.155 --> 00:35:59.950
it would have been disastrous.

384
00:36:01.702 --> 00:36:04.580
Do you think he'll wake up by tonight?

385
00:36:04.663 --> 00:36:06.790
Of course. He'll be up soon.

386
00:36:07.499 --> 00:36:10.294
Well. I'll let you rest.

387
00:36:11.253 --> 00:36:14.673
If there's anything I can do.
please call anytime.

388
00:36:14.756 --> 00:36:15.591
Of course.

389
00:36:26.393 --> 00:36:27.853
That bodyguard...

390
00:36:29.396 --> 00:36:31.148
If he wakes up and talks nonsense.

391
00:36:32.524 --> 00:36:33.525
won't it be a problem?

392
00:36:35.569 --> 00:36:37.738
I really am going to use him as an agent.

393
00:36:38.655 --> 00:36:39.740
You think he'll accept?

394
00:36:40.490 --> 00:36:41.366
Accept the job?

395
00:36:42.159 --> 00:36:43.619
Well. I don't know.

396
00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:46.538
Is that really important?

397
00:36:55.422 --> 00:36:57.174
The most dangerous ones

398
00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:01.386
should be kept the closest.

399
00:37:06.767 --> 00:37:07.809
Like Anna.

400
00:37:22.282 --> 00:37:23.241
I can't have Anna

401
00:37:24.910 --> 00:37:26.703
be near you.

402
00:37:55.399 --> 00:37:56.274
Sergeant Kim.

403
00:37:59.861 --> 00:38:00.904
How've you been?

404
00:38:02.280 --> 00:38:03.991
Why so surprised?

405
00:38:04.783 --> 00:38:06.243
Lighten up. will you?

406
00:38:08.954 --> 00:38:10.789
What's all this?

407
00:38:10.872 --> 00:38:12.290
-Gosh.
-Sir!

408
00:38:13.417 --> 00:38:14.251
It's all right.

409
00:38:15.043 --> 00:38:17.254
These are useless anyway.

410
00:38:20.632 --> 00:38:23.760
And can you wait outside?

411
00:38:26.388 --> 00:38:28.682
What are you doing? I said wait outside.

412
00:38:39.860 --> 00:38:41.486
Attacking the origin. Traps.

413
00:38:46.867 --> 00:38:48.368
It was you. Lieutenant Colonel.

414
00:38:48.702 --> 00:38:49.786
Hey. man.

415
00:38:50.912 --> 00:38:52.414
I was discharged as colonel.

416
00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:56.168
And I was discharged as a private.

417
00:38:58.587 --> 00:39:00.964
I'm sorry. I had no power to prevent that.

418
00:39:01.298 --> 00:39:02.299
It wasn't about power.

419
00:39:03.425 --> 00:39:04.760
It just wasn't your goal.

420
00:39:08.055 --> 00:39:11.016
I found that you need power
to achieve goals.

421
00:39:21.026 --> 00:39:21.860
Yoo-jin!

422
00:39:22.611 --> 00:39:24.279
Who did this to you?

423
00:39:24.529 --> 00:39:25.363
Are you okay?

424
00:39:25.447 --> 00:39:28.742
Can you have some manners
and knock when you visit next time?

425
00:39:29.659 --> 00:39:30.494
Sorry.

426
00:39:33.288 --> 00:39:34.164
You're here. too.

427
00:39:36.083 --> 00:39:37.334
How have you been?

428
00:39:37.876 --> 00:39:38.835
Same as always.

429
00:39:41.963 --> 00:39:44.132
Are you okay? Did Park Gwan-su do this?

430
00:39:44.674 --> 00:39:46.551
-I don't know.
-No. he did.

431
00:39:47.052 --> 00:39:49.304
It's got him written all over it.

432
00:39:49.387 --> 00:39:50.514
That asshole...

433
00:39:53.850 --> 00:39:56.103
I just cursed.

434
00:39:56.186 --> 00:39:57.187
How rude of me.

435
00:39:58.480 --> 00:39:59.397
Chairman Choi.

436
00:40:00.273 --> 00:40:02.275
If you want to seem refined.

437
00:40:02.901 --> 00:40:05.654
shouldn't you address me
by my appropriate title?

438
00:40:05.737 --> 00:40:07.656
I really don't want to do that.

439
00:40:08.115 --> 00:40:10.200
It feels awkward and distant.

440
00:40:10.283 --> 00:40:11.827
No way.

441
00:40:12.369 --> 00:40:16.540
But it's not like
we're that close anyways.

442
00:40:22.212 --> 00:40:23.380
Sir.

443
00:40:23.463 --> 00:40:25.632
It's almost time. The film crew's here.

444
00:40:25.715 --> 00:40:26.550
Really?

445
00:40:27.676 --> 00:40:29.136
Well. then.

446
00:40:29.219 --> 00:40:31.763
Enjoy your visit with your dear sister.

447
00:40:32.430 --> 00:40:34.224
I should get going.

448
00:40:35.559 --> 00:40:38.019
Good luck. Se-joon. You got this.

449
00:40:39.020 --> 00:40:39.896
I got this.

450
00:40:40.939 --> 00:40:42.399
Come here for a second.

451
00:40:45.026 --> 00:40:45.861
Me?

452
00:40:51.908 --> 00:40:52.784
What is it?

453
00:40:53.660 --> 00:40:54.786
Closer.

454
00:41:25.066 --> 00:41:27.819
You've been nursing your wife all night.

455
00:41:28.445 --> 00:41:29.863
You should look the part.

456
00:41:37.871 --> 00:41:41.208
You really are an amazing wife and mother.

457
00:41:43.293 --> 00:41:44.502
But you don't have kids.

458
00:41:45.795 --> 00:41:47.255
So scratch the mother part.

459
00:42:00.727 --> 00:42:03.688
Stay one step behind me.

460
00:42:13.907 --> 00:42:16.034
Sir. how is your wife?

461
00:42:16.117 --> 00:42:17.535
Who do you think did this?

462
00:42:17.619 --> 00:42:19.537
Have you spoken with Park Gwan-su?

463
00:42:19.621 --> 00:42:22.457
Please. sir. Give us word.

464
00:42:41.101 --> 00:42:43.853
You wanted a word?

465
00:43:03.999 --> 00:43:05.041
Because of me.

466
00:43:07.210 --> 00:43:09.337
my wife was brought to the brink of death.

467
00:43:11.006 --> 00:43:12.799
and I looked after her all night.

468
00:43:17.137 --> 00:43:20.181
So what could I possibly say?

469
00:43:22.726 --> 00:43:26.730
All she does is care for others.

470
00:43:27.814 --> 00:43:31.609
Frightened. while on painkillers
and sleeping pills.

471
00:43:32.193 --> 00:43:35.822
she tossed and turned all night
as she struggled to sleep.

472
00:43:37.782 --> 00:43:39.576
And all I could do was watch.

473
00:43:40.410 --> 00:43:42.037
I'm a terrible husband.

474
00:43:46.082 --> 00:43:49.461
What do you want me to say?

475
00:43:56.301 --> 00:43:57.969
{\an8}JANG SHARES HONEST THOUGHTS

476
00:43:58.970 --> 00:44:01.389
They added background music
to a live broadcast?

477
00:44:01.473 --> 00:44:02.432
<i>-My wife...</i>
-Wow.

478
00:44:03.391 --> 00:44:06.144
<i>has given up everything for me.</i>

479
00:44:07.145 --> 00:44:08.229
Despite being

480
00:44:08.813 --> 00:44:11.274
an heiress to her family's fortune.

481
00:44:11.524 --> 00:44:13.485
she gave up all of those privileges

482
00:44:14.778 --> 00:44:17.906
to become the wife of a poor politician.

483
00:44:20.241 --> 00:44:22.118
My wife has faced many hardships.

484
00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:25.288
In my youth.

485
00:44:25.997 --> 00:44:28.917
I was a such a selfish man.

486
00:44:29.834 --> 00:44:33.004
I wanted to be a part
of the labor and democracy movements.

487
00:44:33.088 --> 00:44:36.383
so I spent many nights in cold jail cells.

488
00:44:41.638 --> 00:44:44.265
And I made her suffer through it.

489
00:44:46.059 --> 00:44:47.811
Angered by the world.

490
00:44:48.395 --> 00:44:50.897
all I did was act out.

491
00:44:52.232 --> 00:44:55.777
And I did not see her reaching out for me.

492
00:44:58.446 --> 00:45:00.198
Because of her family's wealth.

493
00:45:02.033 --> 00:45:04.661
I couldn't accept her heart.

494
00:45:06.496 --> 00:45:07.789
I was that foolish.

495
00:45:11.876 --> 00:45:13.211
But my wife...

496
00:45:15.880 --> 00:45:17.632
is a brave person.

497
00:45:19.092 --> 00:45:21.469
She gave up everything she had...

498
00:45:25.432 --> 00:45:27.267
And for someone with nothing like me.

499
00:45:29.018 --> 00:45:30.645
{\an8}she loved me.

500
00:45:31.604 --> 00:45:32.522
Wow.

501
00:45:33.481 --> 00:45:35.733
Se-joon's an amazing actor.

502
00:45:35.817 --> 00:45:37.569
It's totally believable.

503
00:45:44.576 --> 00:45:45.410
<i>Because...</i>

504
00:45:47.078 --> 00:45:48.621
<i>it's the truth.</i>

505
00:45:49.205 --> 00:45:52.625
<i>I could not protect my innocent wife.</i>

506
00:45:53.084 --> 00:45:55.962
And I despised myself for that.

507
00:45:56.588 --> 00:46:01.468
Am I even worthy enough

508
00:46:01.551 --> 00:46:05.221
to share the burden
of 50 million people...

509
00:46:07.682 --> 00:46:08.975
as that position calls for?

510
00:46:12.770 --> 00:46:14.147
But even before that.

511
00:46:16.107 --> 00:46:20.528
do I dare ask my wife.
who's still terrified

512
00:46:21.279 --> 00:46:22.655
as she lies in bed.

513
00:46:23.573 --> 00:46:27.744
to keep walking down this path

514
00:46:30.079 --> 00:46:31.456
with me?

515
00:46:45.011 --> 00:46:47.472
From this day forward.

516
00:46:49.224 --> 00:46:50.934
all of my political activities

517
00:46:52.060 --> 00:46:53.686
as a presidential candidate...

518
00:47:03.238 --> 00:47:04.155
will cease.

519
00:47:05.657 --> 00:47:06.574
What?

520
00:47:09.536 --> 00:47:10.954
-What is he saying?
-What?

521
00:47:15.542 --> 00:47:18.336
Are you saying
you're retiring from politics?

522
00:47:28.721 --> 00:47:30.473
-No!
-You can't!

523
00:47:30.557 --> 00:47:32.684
-You can't quit!
-No!

524
00:47:54.080 --> 00:47:55.039
Instead.

525
00:47:56.499 --> 00:47:57.500
I will now

526
00:47:58.376 --> 00:48:00.587
take up a new fight.

527
00:48:01.421 --> 00:48:05.717
I will fight against those who heinously
use terrorism against the opposition.

528
00:48:06.175 --> 00:48:07.760
those who attack

529
00:48:08.636 --> 00:48:10.930
our innocent wives and children.

530
00:48:11.264 --> 00:48:14.100
and those who trample
on the socially vulnerable!

531
00:48:14.601 --> 00:48:19.397
I will fight every single act
of terror in Korea!

532
00:48:21.024 --> 00:48:22.984
As a politician.

533
00:48:23.192 --> 00:48:24.986
I will do everything in my power

534
00:48:25.612 --> 00:48:27.655
to fight evil!

535
00:48:28.323 --> 00:48:29.866
This is more meaningful

536
00:48:30.783 --> 00:48:31.951
than being president.

537
00:48:33.369 --> 00:48:36.205
And it is something I can do

538
00:48:36.623 --> 00:48:38.583
even if I'm not president.

539
00:48:38.666 --> 00:48:40.001
-That's right!
-That's right!

540
00:48:40.084 --> 00:48:42.253
Jang Se-joon!

541
00:48:42.337 --> 00:48:44.756
-That is something I can do
-Jang Se-joon!

542
00:48:44.839 --> 00:48:47.508
-even if I wasn't a politician.
-Jang for president!

543
00:48:48.009 --> 00:48:51.220
This is something we all can do!

544
00:48:51.304 --> 00:48:52.388
Jang for president!

545
00:48:52.472 --> 00:48:55.933
And I will stand on your side.

546
00:48:56.017 --> 00:48:58.311
Jang for president!

547
00:48:58.394 --> 00:49:01.314
-I will stand with all of you
-Jang for president!

548
00:49:02.106 --> 00:49:06.152
and win this fight!

549
00:49:11.074 --> 00:49:13.826
Jang for president!

550
00:49:13.910 --> 00:49:16.704
-Yes!
-Jang for president!

551
00:49:16.788 --> 00:49:23.795
Jang for president!

552
00:49:28.633 --> 00:49:35.181
{\an8}<i>Jang for president!</i>

553
00:49:35.264 --> 00:49:36.849
-<i>Jang for president!</i>
-He's good.

554
00:49:36.933 --> 00:49:37.975
<i>Jang for president!</i>

555
00:49:38.059 --> 00:49:39.477
He's lost his conscience...

556
00:49:40.395 --> 00:49:41.604
<i>Jang for president!</i>

557
00:49:41.688 --> 00:49:43.314
But he has a way with people.

558
00:49:48.319 --> 00:49:51.489
Yes. a rather shocking announcement.

559
00:49:51.572 --> 00:49:53.241
Your thoughts. Assemblyman Kim?

560
00:49:53.324 --> 00:49:56.994
It was very shocking.

561
00:49:57.078 --> 00:50:01.958
He's willing to give up the presidency
for his beloved wife... Goodness.

562
00:50:02.917 --> 00:50:04.711
Well. that remains to be seen.

563
00:50:04.794 --> 00:50:08.214
But can we take this as him
pulling out of the presidential race?

564
00:50:08.297 --> 00:50:10.591
What are you saying?

565
00:50:10.675 --> 00:50:13.344
What Assemblyman Jang announced just now

566
00:50:13.428 --> 00:50:16.472
is a declaration of war against violence

567
00:50:16.556 --> 00:50:17.974
and corruption in society.

568
00:50:18.057 --> 00:50:19.016
I guess?

569
00:50:19.100 --> 00:50:24.021
But if he says he's quitting
because of these evils.

570
00:50:24.105 --> 00:50:27.024
that would effectively mean

571
00:50:27.108 --> 00:50:29.527
he's surrendering to them.

572
00:50:30.445 --> 00:50:33.322
Those who committed this act of terror...

573
00:50:37.326 --> 00:50:38.494
Excuse me.

574
00:50:42.165 --> 00:50:44.917
For those who committed
this act of terror.

575
00:50:45.001 --> 00:50:47.378
I'm saying that's what they want.

576
00:50:47.962 --> 00:50:52.175
In my opinion. that can never happen.

577
00:50:52.258 --> 00:50:53.509
I see.

578
00:50:54.051 --> 00:50:58.389
And if by any chance.

579
00:50:58.473 --> 00:51:01.851
Assemblyman Jang's wife. Ms. Choi.

580
00:51:01.934 --> 00:51:03.811
is watching this broadcast.

581
00:51:04.812 --> 00:51:07.482
I would like to tell her something.

582
00:51:08.357 --> 00:51:09.233
And that is?

583
00:51:11.736 --> 00:51:12.570
Stay strong.

584
00:51:13.154 --> 00:51:15.573
And please allow Assemblyman Jang

585
00:51:15.656 --> 00:51:19.702
to return to the people.

586
00:51:20.828 --> 00:51:22.288
I implore you.

587
00:51:23.915 --> 00:51:26.334
Right. We will take a commercial break.

588
00:51:28.586 --> 00:51:30.922
Aren't you sucking up a bit too much?

589
00:51:31.005 --> 00:51:31.881
Hey.

590
00:51:33.966 --> 00:51:35.051
No. I'm not.

591
00:51:35.593 --> 00:51:37.762
I have to do at least this much.

592
00:51:37.845 --> 00:51:40.640
Today will be the turning point
in this election.

593
00:51:42.600 --> 00:51:43.476
You'll see.

594
00:51:49.065 --> 00:51:52.318
{\an8}<i>Jang for president!</i>

595
00:51:52.401 --> 00:51:54.070
-<i>Jang Se-joon!</i>
-Goodness.

596
00:51:54.153 --> 00:51:57.406
<i>Jang for president!</i>

597
00:52:00.952 --> 00:52:01.786
Get the car ready.

598
00:52:03.162 --> 00:52:05.122
-To go where?
-Gosh.

599
00:52:05.498 --> 00:52:08.209
It's only right
to visit her at the hospital.

600
00:52:08.501 --> 00:52:10.211
-Pardon?
-Get my jacket.

601
00:52:11.295 --> 00:52:12.129
Yes. sir.

602
00:52:15.508 --> 00:52:18.427
Jang Se-joon. you rascal.

603
00:52:26.519 --> 00:52:28.104
Here. It's a gift.

604
00:52:30.857 --> 00:52:31.941
What is it?

605
00:52:34.652 --> 00:52:35.695
"Kim Je-ha"?

606
00:52:40.700 --> 00:52:43.494
Jeez. Am I JB Group's puppet now?

607
00:52:45.913 --> 00:52:48.583
Just think of yourself
as a servant of an empire.

608
00:52:49.876 --> 00:52:51.669
Don't worry. It's real.

609
00:52:52.753 --> 00:52:55.798
He disappeared while serving abroad.
There are no issues.

610
00:52:56.090 --> 00:52:58.342
I transferred your fingerprints
to that name.

611
00:52:59.969 --> 00:53:02.388
Just don't apply
for a passport with that name.

612
00:53:03.055 --> 00:53:05.308
Things overseas haven't been resolved yet.

613
00:53:08.352 --> 00:53:09.604
Yoo-jin.

614
00:53:11.480 --> 00:53:13.024
You might actually get elected.

615
00:53:17.194 --> 00:53:19.697
Well. take care of yourself. I'm leaving.

616
00:53:20.698 --> 00:53:21.574
But...

617
00:53:22.825 --> 00:53:24.785
are JB Group's finances bad these days?

618
00:53:25.620 --> 00:53:27.997
Why is the campaign talking about funding?

619
00:53:28.956 --> 00:53:29.999
Oh. that.

620
00:53:30.291 --> 00:53:33.127
People are watching.
We can't just make withdrawals.

621
00:53:33.210 --> 00:53:34.211
Just wait.

622
00:53:34.795 --> 00:53:38.049
Yours takes time because it has to
make its way from overseas.

623
00:53:40.843 --> 00:53:42.470
-Right?
-Of course!

624
00:53:42.762 --> 00:53:43.721
And here I thought...

625
00:53:45.056 --> 00:53:48.392
maybe you didn't want to spend that money.

626
00:53:49.226 --> 00:53:50.519
Of course. I do!

627
00:53:50.603 --> 00:53:53.564
Once you're elected.
you'll pay me back many times over.

628
00:53:56.108 --> 00:53:57.485
No?

629
00:54:03.783 --> 00:54:04.617
See you.

630
00:54:15.044 --> 00:54:17.088
-Hello. sir.
-Hello.

631
00:54:17.546 --> 00:54:20.132
Wait. Why are you armed?

632
00:54:22.301 --> 00:54:24.220
What? Are you arresting me?

633
00:54:24.971 --> 00:54:25.972
Of course not.

634
00:54:26.389 --> 00:54:27.890
After yesterday's incident.

635
00:54:27.974 --> 00:54:31.060
special security measures
for dignitaries were just issued.

636
00:54:31.978 --> 00:54:32.895
Gosh.

637
00:54:33.354 --> 00:54:35.272
All this fuss.

638
00:54:40.736 --> 00:54:43.364
Sir. will you be all right
in enemy territory?

639
00:54:43.447 --> 00:54:46.951
Don't be ridiculous.

640
00:54:47.868 --> 00:54:49.578
Is this camera rolling?

641
00:54:49.662 --> 00:54:50.871
No. it's not.

642
00:54:50.955 --> 00:54:52.581
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

643
00:54:54.125 --> 00:54:56.585
Rumor has it you were behind the attack.

644
00:54:56.669 --> 00:55:00.047
Hey. Why won't anyone target me
with that kind of terrorism?

645
00:55:00.131 --> 00:55:03.384
I can increase my ratings
and get some rest here.

646
00:55:05.261 --> 00:55:07.013
Are you saying this incident

647
00:55:07.096 --> 00:55:09.265
was fabricated by Jang's camp?

648
00:55:09.348 --> 00:55:11.142
Jeez. This again?

649
00:55:11.225 --> 00:55:13.602
Stop spinning stories. okay?

650
00:55:14.228 --> 00:55:15.771
That's a terrible habit.

651
00:55:16.939 --> 00:55:19.483
What. was that a bad joke?

652
00:55:19.567 --> 00:55:20.776
What will you say to Jang?

653
00:55:20.860 --> 00:55:22.319
No. no.

654
00:55:22.403 --> 00:55:24.363
You see. I'm here to visit a patient.

655
00:55:24.655 --> 00:55:26.240
This is very serious.

656
00:55:26.323 --> 00:55:27.992
This should never happen.

657
00:55:28.075 --> 00:55:29.952
I'll see you later. That's enough.

658
00:55:30.369 --> 00:55:31.537
Later.

659
00:55:36.375 --> 00:55:37.209
Goodness.

660
00:55:39.503 --> 00:55:40.838
You must be devastated.

661
00:55:41.672 --> 00:55:42.965
How could this happen?

662
00:55:44.592 --> 00:55:45.718
Well. then.

663
00:55:58.105 --> 00:55:58.939
A bodyguard?

664
00:56:01.484 --> 00:56:04.945
Yeah. You did it before in Iraq.

665
00:56:05.529 --> 00:56:08.908
Gosh. you'll get all kinds
of insurance despite this job crisis.

666
00:56:10.451 --> 00:56:12.036
Since you have prior experience.

667
00:56:12.620 --> 00:56:13.871
your pay will be high too.

668
00:56:14.622 --> 00:56:15.581
Listen. sir.

669
00:56:16.624 --> 00:56:18.417
I have no loyalties to anyone now.

670
00:56:19.794 --> 00:56:21.921
Not to any country or organization.

671
00:56:23.255 --> 00:56:25.758
Loyalty? What's that?

672
00:56:26.383 --> 00:56:27.676
To hell with all that.

673
00:56:28.302 --> 00:56:29.512
I don't need it either.

674
00:56:29.720 --> 00:56:31.806
We just need to do as much as we're paid.

675
00:56:32.473 --> 00:56:34.600
Then. how much do you get paid to do this?

676
00:56:35.851 --> 00:56:38.646
You'll just be used and discarded later.

677
00:56:39.522 --> 00:56:40.356
You know that.

678
00:56:41.816 --> 00:56:43.609
We'll just discard them first then.

679
00:56:52.493 --> 00:56:55.204
You're right. You've changed a lot.

680
00:56:56.831 --> 00:56:58.249
It's the world that's changed.

681
00:57:03.504 --> 00:57:05.798
JSS. the organization I work for.

682
00:57:05.881 --> 00:57:07.633
is not just a security company.

683
00:57:08.634 --> 00:57:11.220
In military terms.
it's a huge information hub.

684
00:57:12.388 --> 00:57:13.556
Internally. you'll find

685
00:57:13.639 --> 00:57:15.558
all of JB Group's trade secrets

686
00:57:15.641 --> 00:57:17.017
and non-transaction details.

687
00:57:17.351 --> 00:57:19.562
Externally.
through the JB Economic Institute.

688
00:57:19.645 --> 00:57:22.314
we collect and monitor intel on the trends

689
00:57:22.398 --> 00:57:24.024
and networks of the elites

690
00:57:24.108 --> 00:57:26.318
in politics. economics. and the media.

691
00:57:26.986 --> 00:57:28.612
These people are pretty powerful.

692
00:57:28.863 --> 00:57:30.531
They'll make it to the Blue House.

693
00:57:31.407 --> 00:57:33.826
Then. you can be pardoned.

694
00:57:41.292 --> 00:57:42.168
Sir.

695
00:57:43.419 --> 00:57:44.253
I'm just...

696
00:57:46.338 --> 00:57:47.882
a defeated soldier. I'm tired.

697
00:57:49.383 --> 00:57:50.426
And now.

698
00:57:51.677 --> 00:57:53.137
I'm just useless.

699
00:57:53.762 --> 00:57:57.057
Why? Because you can't kill anymore?

700
00:58:01.437 --> 00:58:02.605
{\an8}PTSD.

701
00:58:03.439 --> 00:58:04.940
{\an8}We got your background check

702
00:58:05.024 --> 00:58:06.901
{\an8}from Blackstone this morning.

703
00:58:12.114 --> 00:58:14.617
Don't worry. Only I saw it.
Then. I destroyed it.

704
00:58:16.118 --> 00:58:18.871
Our task force survived
after being sent to kill you.

705
00:58:19.747 --> 00:58:20.831
And I found it strange.

706
00:58:21.207 --> 00:58:22.625
If you knew all that.

707
00:58:24.460 --> 00:58:26.545
then why do you want me to join so badly?

708
00:58:28.464 --> 00:58:29.423
Hey. kid.

709
00:58:30.132 --> 00:58:32.968
A bodyguard isn't a murderous mercenary.

710
00:58:35.679 --> 00:58:37.473
You have the natural instincts

711
00:58:37.556 --> 00:58:39.391
of the strongest attacker in battle.

712
00:58:39.975 --> 00:58:41.977
Now. you'll sense the enemy's attacks

713
00:58:42.311 --> 00:58:43.520
as our strongest defender.

714
00:58:45.356 --> 00:58:47.816
And we know you won't hurt your boss now.

715
00:58:49.360 --> 00:58:52.488
You have the best qualifications
to be a bodyguard.

716
00:58:54.823 --> 00:58:56.575
I still have that email.

717
00:58:57.076 --> 00:58:58.619
I think you're forgetting that.

718
00:59:02.331 --> 00:59:03.415
Sergeant Kim.

719
00:59:04.959 --> 00:59:06.210
Let's go to the Blue House.

720
00:59:07.336 --> 00:59:09.463
We can make those shitty military elites

721
00:59:09.713 --> 00:59:11.548
pay for what they did to us.

722
00:59:13.133 --> 00:59:13.968
The Blue House?

723
00:59:15.552 --> 00:59:16.720
Shitty military elites?

724
00:59:17.680 --> 00:59:18.722
You know what?

725
00:59:20.808 --> 00:59:23.102
I can barely even remember now

726
00:59:23.185 --> 00:59:25.229
why I cursed this damn country

727
00:59:25.312 --> 00:59:27.815
and swore to never come back.

728
00:59:30.401 --> 00:59:32.528
And make people pay?

729
00:59:33.112 --> 00:59:34.488
I can't be bothered.

730
00:59:34.822 --> 00:59:36.448
It's just up until the elections.

731
00:59:36.991 --> 00:59:38.534
Work for JSS until then.

732
00:59:39.410 --> 00:59:41.370
Then. no one has to be on guard

733
00:59:41.745 --> 00:59:43.289
or on the run.

734
00:59:46.583 --> 00:59:48.127
I came back because I was tired.

735
00:59:48.210 --> 00:59:49.837
I stopped caring a long time ago.

736
00:59:51.547 --> 00:59:53.048
As long as I'm left alone.

737
00:59:53.882 --> 00:59:55.384
no one else will get hurt.

738
00:59:56.635 --> 01:00:00.264
I'll delete that email
after the elections.

739
01:00:00.723 --> 01:00:01.557
Sergeant Kim.

740
01:00:03.225 --> 01:00:04.059
Sergeant Kim!

741
01:00:35.507 --> 01:00:37.384
How are you feeling?

742
01:00:37.718 --> 01:00:39.011
Better. thanks to you.

743
01:00:43.223 --> 01:00:45.476
PRESIDENT KIM JEONG-HUN
GET WELL SOON

744
01:00:46.060 --> 01:00:46.935
I was thankful

745
01:00:48.228 --> 01:00:50.481
that the presidential secretary came by.

746
01:00:51.231 --> 01:00:52.316
Is that so?

747
01:00:52.524 --> 01:00:53.484
Goodness.

748
01:00:54.318 --> 01:00:56.779
The chief of staff
should've came in person.

749
01:00:57.738 --> 01:00:59.448
-Goodness...
-It's all right.

750
01:00:59.531 --> 01:01:01.408
They're busy people. And I'm just...

751
01:01:01.492 --> 01:01:03.118
No. that's not right.

752
01:01:03.202 --> 01:01:06.663
I'm sure he eats <i>cheonggukjang</i>
like us regular people do.

753
01:01:06.747 --> 01:01:09.375
It's just not right. How thoughtless.

754
01:01:09.792 --> 01:01:11.710
That man has a lot of integrity.

755
01:01:12.169 --> 01:01:14.296
Why would he visit a nobody like me?

756
01:01:15.381 --> 01:01:17.091
-Is that so?
-Of course.

757
01:01:17.633 --> 01:01:22.054
Right. Now that I think of it.
you came by often

758
01:01:22.679 --> 01:01:25.140
to have some of our <i>cheonggukjang</i>

759
01:01:25.224 --> 01:01:26.975
when my father was alive.

760
01:01:31.021 --> 01:01:34.650
And we don't serve it that much anymore.

761
01:01:35.651 --> 01:01:36.693
It smells foul.

762
01:01:39.029 --> 01:01:41.490
It was pretty delicious.

763
01:01:43.992 --> 01:01:45.911
Looking back. your father was

764
01:01:45.994 --> 01:01:48.288
quite an insightful man. wasn't he?

765
01:01:48.372 --> 01:01:50.416
He could see far ahead into the future

766
01:01:50.499 --> 01:01:54.336
and selected the current young chairman
as his successor.

767
01:02:03.554 --> 01:02:06.140
Anyways. I wish you a speedy recovery.

768
01:02:06.598 --> 01:02:08.725
I must get going.

769
01:02:08.809 --> 01:02:11.103
I'm sorry I can't see you out.

770
01:02:11.186 --> 01:02:13.564
Goodness. Please. don't be.

771
01:02:33.417 --> 01:02:35.127
She's a bold bitch.

772
01:02:36.086 --> 01:02:37.212
Very bold.

773
01:04:32.244 --> 01:04:33.495
THE K2

774
01:04:33.996 --> 01:04:36.873
{\an8}Agent Kim Je-ha
will be joining our VIP team.

775
01:04:37.666 --> 01:04:40.627
<i>As long as Ms. Choi
is alive on this earth.</i>

776
01:04:40.711 --> 01:04:41.962
<i>no one will ever come here.</i>

777
01:04:42.045 --> 01:04:43.755
<i>It's not that he won't.</i>

778
01:04:43.839 --> 01:04:46.133
<i>He can't come because of her.</i>

779
01:04:47.050 --> 01:04:50.762
<i>There's a lot of cameras around.
How about a wave before we go?</i>

780
01:04:53.390 --> 01:04:56.977
You put the hound
in the cage with the other hounds.

780
01:04:57.305 --> 01:05:57.492
